\section*{Histologic Features}

The organizing pneumonia pattern is patchy and consists of polypoid plugs of loose organizing connective tissue involving alveolar ducts and alveoli with or without bronchiolar intraluminal polyps (Fig. 4.3) [8,20,21]. The lung architecture is preserved. The majority of changes are centered on small airways. A small amount of airspace fibrin may be focally present.

