Pulmonary function tests in COP reveal reductions in lung volumes (forced vital capacity [FVC] and total lung capacity [TLC]) and diffusing capacity for carbon monoxide ( $\mathrm{DL}_{\mathrm{CO}}$ ), and a widened alveolar-arterial oxygen gradient [6,13,14,37,39].
