\section*{Conclusion}

Sarcoidosis is one of the most common idiopathic interstitial lung diseases. Although the prognosis for patients is often good, there is a subset of chronic disease. These patients often require years of corticosteroids and steroid-sparing agents to control their disease. Pulmonary hypertension is a frequent complication of advanced pulmonary disease. Some of the treatments for idiopathic pulmonary arterial hypertension have also been successful in treating sarcoidosis associated pulmonary arterial hypertension.

